parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine overheating, stalling, and potential engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The coolant light comes on
the engine overheats
the vehicle stalls
coolant leaks into the engine
and a sweet or burning smell is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight lens can cause reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and premature bulb failure, which can lead to a loss of lighting and compromise safety.
symptoms: The headlight lens is cloudy or yellowed
the lens cover falls off
moisture or water enters the headlight assembly
the bulb blows out
and the headlight is dim or inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight seal can cause moisture or water to enter the headlight assembly, leading to premature bulb failure, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Moisture or water enters the headlight assembly
the headlight lens is cloudy or fogged
the bulb blows out
and the headlight is dim or inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight adhesive can cause the lens cover to fall off, leading to premature bulb failure, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlight lens cover falls off
the bulb blows out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door can cause the door to open or close unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or trapping occupants inside the vehicle. This can also lead to a loss of control while driving, especially if the door opens suddenly.
symptoms: The power sliding door opens or closes unexpectedly
the door fails to latch or close properly
the door alarm sounds while the door is closed
the door opens or closes intermittently
the door rattles or makes excessive noise
the door fails to operate electronically or manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door lock can cause the door to open or unlock unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or trapping occupants inside the vehicle. This can also lead to a loss of control while driving, especially if the door opens suddenly.
symptoms: The sliding door lock locks or unlocks while the vehicle is in motion
the door fails to latch or close properly
the door alarm sounds while the door is closed
the door opens or closes intermittently
the door rattles or makes excessive noise.
